# VPN client list for the ger panel — fully SOPS-encrypted (client identities are PII and
# this is a public repo). The whole list is one `clients:` block-scalar STRING so SOPS hides
# even the map keys/handles (it can't encrypt YAML keys directly). Create the real file:
#   cd terraform/live/threexui/ger
#   cp clients.sops.yaml.example clients.sops.yaml
#   sops clients.sops.yaml          # edit the inner YAML (it opens decrypted); save → re-encrypts
#   # (or: $EDITOR clients.sops.yaml then `sops --encrypt --in-place clients.sops.yaml`)
#
# Inside the block, each map key is the client handle (stable → it's the Terraform for_each
# key; the panel client `email` should match it). Per client:
#   inbound_key (required) → a key in the unit's `inbounds`; email (required, unique per panel);
#   optional flow / enable / total_gb / expiry_time / limit_ip / comment / tg_id / sub_id.
clients: |
  client-a:
    inbound_key: reality
    email: client-a
    comment: owner
